Mexico (3 states). 4 Mar 2015. Dengue (conf.) by state: Guerrero 280
cases, Chiapas 120 cases, Quintana Roo 96 cases divided nearly equally between classical dengue fever and DHF.
http://sipse.com/novedades/se-registraron-96-casos-de-dengue-en-quintana-roo-en-2014-140364.html [in Spanish]

[With half of the total cases reported as DHF, either there is significant underreporting of non-DHF cases or a less strict clinical definition of DHF in practice.

